entry.title: Use SEQUENCE_CHECKER in ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper
entry.content:
Currently ResourceLoadInfoNotifierWrapper uses a THREAD_CHECKER to

ensure that all member methods are called from a same single thread.

This is intended to protect `resource_load_info_`. (This check was

introduced at https://crrev.com/c/2402321/31..32.) But we are planing to

call the member methods from non-single thread task runner for the off

the main thread resource loading project. So this CL changes it to use a

SEQUENCE_CHECKER.



This CL doesn't introduce any behavior change.

entry.title: [Track Stats] Implement the stats cache.
entry.content:
This CL makes it so that stats are only updated if this is the first

time in the task execution cycle that the getters are invoked,

preserving JS run-to-completion semantics, and otherwise returns

cached values.



This CL also moves the responsibility of maybe-updating into the

MediaStreamTrackVideoStats interface. This allows keeping direct

references to the stats object and calling videoStats.totalFrames etc

directly without first calling track.videoStats, as was previously

required (a bug).



WPTs for both features are added.

entry.title: PageLoadMetrics: Update PreviewPageLoadMetricsObserver
entry.content:
Add a new PageVisitType, kHistoryVisit, to represent the case

where the page navigation happens through the back forward

interfaces.

visit, and reported as kOrigin or kIndependent type visit

if it doesn't hit the BFCache.

Nothing is changed for the BFCache hit case, not reporting

separate reports for restored visits.

entry.title: Fix client window freeze when starting gestures with more than 2 fingers
entry.content:
When a gesture with more than 2 fingers (e.g. 3-finger pinch) starts on

a client window (e.g. Lacros PiP window), it leads to an inconsistent

state and the window becomes immovable until the window is closed.



This commit removes the code that was updating the `gesture_target_` to

`nullptr` in `ToplevelWindowEventHandler::CompleteDrag()`.

`gesture_target_` should not be updated to `nullptr` in `CompleteDrag()`

because:



- the existence of `gesture_target_` is used elsewhere to determine if

an ongoing event has originated from a touchscreen or a mouse, and



- `CompleteDrag()` is called even when a gesture hasn't completely ended

(i.e. when at least one finger is still on the screen, like when a

more-than-2-finger gesture starts).



If the gesture successfully completes then

`UpdateGestureTarget(nullptr)` is called when the last finger leaves the

screen in `ToplevelWindowEventHandler` anyways, so it should be

unnecessary to call it in `CompleteDrag()`.



Bug: b/301013053

Test: manually verified that the window stays movable after

more-than-2-finger gestures

entry.title: Add tests to confirm the network error in ServiceWorkerAutoPreload
entry.content:
This CL adds a unit test for the network error case in

ServiceWorkerAutoPreload. We had a crash bug due to the unexpected

state transition from State::kResponseReceived to State::kCompleted.

This was fixed in [1], but the test was not added. The new unit test in

this CL confirms the transition works as intended.



This transition could happen when below conditions are all met:

1) SWAutoPreload is enabled.

2) The fetch handler result is fallback.

3) The initial response is successfully received.

4) The response is not transered into the data pipe yet for teeing.

5) The response is completed with the network error.



[1] https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4835496

entry.title: Improve column balancing for IFC-floats.
entry.content:
Space shortage caused by float breaks wasn't propagated correctly for

floats inside an inline formatting context, resulting in column

balancing problems, typically over-stretching.



Let PositionFloat() create a break-before break token, instead of

requiring every call site to do it. Also propagate space shortage here.



This required that space shortage propagation code were moved up from

NGBoxFragmentBuilder to NGFragmentBuilder, so that it can be used with

NGLineBoxFragmentBuilder can use it as well. Since this is closely tied

with another column balancing concept - tallest unbreakable block-size -

also move that one.



Add two tests: One for floats as block children. This was already

working, but there was no test coverage. The other test is for floats as

inline children, and this wasn't working without this CL.

entry.title: PDF a11y: Create the status node to notify users of PDF content loading
entry.content:
Make the status node available regardless of the PDF OCR feature to

notify users of PDF content loading. This status node will be added and

become available when it starts to load PDF content into an a11y tree.

Then, the status node will be deleted once it finishes loading the

PDF content into the tree.



Note that this status node will be kept when PDF OCR is on and PDF

doesn't have accessible text but images without alternative text.



This notification is necessary especially when users open a large PDF

(e.g. 200 or more pages) as it takes one or more minutes to load such

a large PDF. Without notification, users won't have any accessible

information that helps them know what's going on after opening a PDF

until it finishes loading the PDF content into an a11y tree.

entry.title: [TSF] Deny lock to TEXT_INPUT_TYPE_NONE in RequestLock.
entry.content:
There are scenarios where the text input type can switch to NONE before the composition can be cancelled by TSF. In these cases we deny the document lock in RequestLock API by returning E_FAIL. This is similar to what we do for dummy TSF text stores.

e.g.

- UpdateTextInputState is called that switches the text input to NONE.

- Calls InputMethodWinTSF::OnTextInputTypeChanged that first tries to cancel the composition if there is any.

- This reentrantly calls into TSF's RequestLock API where it tries to commit previously composed text, but the text input type has already switched to NONE, so it fails in the text input client.



Bug: 1483978
